Definition_e: Lower than surrounding land beyond a 50 m radius, with no surface outlet for water
Slope less than 3 degrees and not a hilltop, ridge, valley bottom or depression
Higher than all or nearly all of the surrounding land beyond a 50 m radius
As for hilltop but elongated and extending beyond a 50 m radius
Neither crest nor depression or valley bottom, and with slope more than 3 degrees
Lower than nearly all of surrounding land beyond a 50 m radius, but water can flow out
A depression located along the axial trend of an anticline; an area confined on two sides by downward slopes and on two sides by upward slopes.
